 Build instructions (with cmake):
 -------------------------------

 1st: edit the file BuildSetup.cmake according to your
      system setup.
 
 2nd: type the following commands:
 
    $ mkdir build
    $ cd build
    $ cmake -C ../BuildSetup.cmake ..
    $ make install

 For more information on CMake for the ILCSoftware check:
 http://www-flc.desy.de/ilcsoft/ (will be available soon!)

 CMake's official website:
 http://www.cmake.org


 Build instructions (old makefiles): -> Deprecated, please use cmake!
 --------------------------------------------------------------------
 
 edit env.sh according to your system setup

 # need current version from cvs, at least tag lccdv00-01 !!
 export LCIO=~gaede/lcio/devel/v01-04beta
 
 # your installation of CondDBMySQL
 # requires a runnig mysql server initialized for CondDBMySQL
 export CondDBMySQL=/data/gaede/CondDBMySQL
 
 # path to mysql
 export MYSQL_PATH=/opt/products/mysql/3.23.58
 
  . env.sh
 
 cd source
 gmake 
 
 # create API documentation in ./doc/html/index.html
 gmake doc 

 --------------------------------------------------------------------


Make sure you have a version of CondDBMySQL with tag CondDBMySQLLisbon-0-5-6
or higher as this contains important bug fixes.


Run examples:  ( see code in source/test ) , e.g.

 ./test/createcalfile hcal.slcio hcal

 ./test/readcalfile hcal.slcio hcal


 ./test/calfiletodb hcal.slcio hcal myhcal 100 200
 ./test/calfiletodb hcal.slcio hcal myhcal 200 300
 ./test/calfiletodb hcal.slcio hcal myhcal 300 400
 ./test/calfiletodb hcal.slcio hcal myhcal 400 500

 ./test/tagdbfolder /lccd/myhcal mytag01 "just a test tag"

 
 ./test/calfiletodb hcal.slcio hcal myhcal 0 500


 ./test/calfilefromdb myhcal 20 fromdb.slcio mytag01


 ./test/calfilefromdb myhcal 20 fromdb.slcio 


